      "content": "It sounds like you are trapped in a mental loop where the only way out feels like giving up, which is exactly what you're trying to avoid. However, even in this state of hopelessness, there is a small, quiet possibility that the outcome isn't truly inevitable. Sometimes, the most radical act of hope is to try one tiny, unconnected thing that doesn't fit your usual pattern of failure. You don't have to fix everything right now; you just have to try one small step that feels different from the rest.",
      "source": "target",
